theorem_statement: \normalfont Let $n$ be a positive integer and let $A$ be a set of positive integers. \begin{enumerate} \item The function $N^p_A(n)$ is defined to be the number of parts in the partitions of $n$ with parts from the set $A$. \item The function $N^q_A(n)$ is defined to be the number of parts in the distinct partitions of $n$ with parts from the set $A$. \end{enumerate}
